==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unify
<hw>U"ni*fy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Unified</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Unifying</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[<ets>Uni-</ets> +
<ets>-fy</ets>: cf. F. <ets>unifier</ets>.]</ety> <def>To cause to be
one; to make into a unit; to unite; to view as one.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A comprehensive or <qex>unifying</qex> act of the judging
faculty.</q> <rj><qau>De Quincey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Perception is thus a <qex>unifying</qex> act.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W.
Hamilton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unigeniture</ent>⟦br⟧
